<h2 style="font-size:18px;">Bangladesh Exports Grow Despite Factory Closures</h2>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The Bangladesh Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Association (BGMEA) says that over 200 factories in <a href="/quality-control-bangladesh">Bangladesh</a> have been shut down since the collapse of Rana Plaza last year, costing millions in export revenue and thousands of jobs.<a href="#footnotes" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup style="font-size: 10px;">7</sup></a></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The trend is likely to continue until standards improve. AI data shows that while we saw a rise in audits performed, 38.7% of manufacturing and 16.4% of <a href="/ethical-audit">ethical audits</a> have failed so far this year in <a href="/quality-control-bangladesh">Bangladesh</a>, whereas 23.9% and 11.1% failed in 2013, respectively. Exports from the country grew by 13% year-on-year between January and May, with over 66% of exports going to Europe and the United States.<a href="#footnotes" style="text-decoration: none;"><sup style="font-size: 10px;">8</sup></a></p>

